1. Steady the steel: Start by holding the knife in your cutting hand (or dominant hand) and your honing steel in the other. Place the honing steel tip down on a steady surface like a cutting board. 
2. Find your best angle: Place the heel of the knife (where the end meets the handle) at the top of the steel. Angle slightly so the sharp edge of the knife hits the steel at approximately 20 degrees. 
3. Proceed smooth and steady: Starting slow, run the blade of the knife down the steel, moving the knife from the heel to the tip using light pressure. Repeat with the other side, completing about 5 strokes per side.. 

Let us know how it goes! 

 

